# Suvo, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Suvo () is a rural locality (a selo) in Barguzinsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 382 as of 2010. There are seven streets.
Geography
Suvo is located 45&nbsp;km east of Barguzin (the district's administrative centre) by road. Bodon is the nearest rural locality.
